TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {20260=The first Saturday of each month enjoy a casual afternoon for knitters, crocheters, spinners and weavers from beginners to pros. Come and learn a new skill or come and share skills and talents with others. Between 1:00 and 3:00 bring the projects you are currently working on and enjoy the companionship and knowledge of other fiber enthusiasts at the Stewartsville Library.  This free program is open to teens and adults. For more information please call the Stewartsville Library 540-425-7008 ext 3., 27991=Copyright © 2015}
